stylometry:
The total cost of managing a product in inventory involves both the ordering cost and the holding costs associated with the product.  The holding costs are calculated by: (demand / average inventory quantity)*cost of ordering.  The ordering costs are calculated by: (average inventory*cost of holding).
When managing inventory, we must weigh the cost of holding inventory (storage, spoilage, etc.) against the cost of a stock out.  We need to keep enough supply on hand to satisfy the demand of our customers without incurring losses due to overstocking and spoilage.
